1
00:00:03,503 --> 00:00:04,795
Nakamura...

2
00:00:04,796 --> 00:00:06,590
Do you remember me?

3
00:00:08,383 --> 00:00:09,718
It's me, Kasuga.

4
00:00:10,594 --> 00:00:11,887
Takao Kasuga.

5
00:00:13,805 --> 00:00:15,474
I came to see you.

6
00:00:32,324 --> 00:00:33,784
What's that face for?

7
00:00:36,662 --> 00:00:38,038
Long time no see.

8
00:00:39,498 --> 00:00:40,958
Long time no see...

9
00:00:43,627 --> 00:00:45,379
What are you standing there for?

10
00:00:45,963 --> 00:00:48,632
Go ahead and eat. It's good.

11
00:00:53,345 --> 00:00:54,346
Uh...

12
00:00:55,180 --> 00:00:56,431
So...

13
00:00:57,349 --> 00:00:58,475
You're Kasuga.

14
00:00:59,685 --> 00:01:01,520
Thanks for coming all this way.

15
00:01:03,063 --> 00:01:04,439
I'm Sawa's mother.

16
00:01:09,653 --> 00:01:11,071
I'm sorry, but,

17
00:01:12,906 --> 00:01:14,408
I want you...

18
00:01:15,534 --> 00:01:17,244
to leave Sawa alone.

19
00:01:20,789 --> 00:01:22,165
She's finally...

20
00:01:23,166 --> 00:01:24,960
found peace with things.

21
00:01:26,587 --> 00:01:28,297
It's just her and me now.

22
00:01:33,969 --> 00:01:35,178
I hope you can understand.

23
00:01:37,723 --> 00:01:38,765
Of course.

24
00:01:50,027 --> 00:01:51,194
Sawa!

25
00:01:52,029 --> 00:01:55,072
Kasuga told me about you,
and I came all this way

26
00:01:55,073 --> 00:01:57,450
because I wanted to meet you!

27
00:01:57,451 --> 00:02:01,245
I don't know how you feel about Kasuga,

28
00:02:01,246 --> 00:02:03,874
or it all might not matter to you anymore,

29
00:02:04,791 --> 00:02:07,877
but can we talk outside for a bit?

30
00:02:07,878 --> 00:02:09,796
I'm so sorry to bother you like this!

31
00:02:11,089 --> 00:02:12,299
Tokiwa...

32
00:02:17,304 --> 00:02:18,555
Sure.

33
00:02:19,765 --> 00:02:22,059
But first, eat.

34
00:02:22,559 --> 00:02:23,977
Then, we'll talk.

35
00:03:25,705 --> 00:03:27,958
THE FLOWERS OF EVIL

36
00:03:31,920 --> 00:03:35,257
FINAL EPISODE

37
00:03:37,134 --> 00:03:38,760
Kasuga,

38
00:03:39,428 --> 00:03:41,555
don't leave anything half-done, okay?

39
00:03:42,597 --> 00:03:45,767
That's what I hate the most.

40
00:03:47,269 --> 00:03:48,353
Okay.

41
00:03:51,565 --> 00:03:53,400
Make sure you don't regret it later.

42
00:03:55,026 --> 00:03:56,027
All right.

43
00:04:05,036 --> 00:04:06,413
Nakamura.

44
00:04:12,461 --> 00:04:13,628
So...

45
00:04:14,713 --> 00:04:17,048
you live with your mother now?

46
00:04:17,674 --> 00:04:19,301
That's right.

47
00:04:22,804 --> 00:04:24,556
What happened to your dad?

48
00:04:27,434 --> 00:04:29,144
Nakamura...

49
00:04:30,520 --> 00:04:31,688
Since that day,

50
00:04:33,857 --> 00:04:36,067
how have you been living your life?

51
00:04:37,194 --> 00:04:38,612
I don't remember.

52
00:04:39,404 --> 00:04:41,823
It doesn't matter anymore.

53
00:04:49,456 --> 00:04:50,624
Look.

54
00:04:55,170 --> 00:04:58,548
In this town, the sun sets into the sea.

55
00:04:59,674 --> 00:05:01,051
But after a while,

56
00:05:01,593 --> 00:05:03,720
it comes up from the sea on that side.

57
00:05:04,387 --> 00:05:06,890
Forever and ever.

58
00:05:07,474 --> 00:05:09,643
Round and round.

59
00:05:10,519 --> 00:05:12,979
It's beautiful, isn't it?

60
00:05:15,774 --> 00:05:16,983
I don't know.

61
00:05:19,319 --> 00:05:20,904
That day,

62
00:05:22,030 --> 00:05:24,406
on the riverbank
on our way to the summer festival,

63
00:05:24,407 --> 00:05:26,785
you saw the sunset
and said it was "beautiful."

64
00:05:29,120 --> 00:05:31,248
Is that sky and this sky

65
00:05:32,499 --> 00:05:33,583
the same to you?

66
00:05:40,507 --> 00:05:41,758
Nakamura,

67
00:05:44,719 --> 00:05:46,429
there's something I want to ask you.

68
00:05:51,977 --> 00:05:53,061
That night,

69
00:05:54,563 --> 00:05:56,773
why did you shove me away?

70
00:06:04,573 --> 00:06:05,740
Who knows?

71
00:06:07,284 --> 00:06:08,743
I've forgotten.

72
00:06:34,269 --> 00:06:35,728
Are you...

73
00:06:35,729 --> 00:06:37,272
dating her?

74
00:06:38,398 --> 00:06:39,983
That person.

75
00:06:50,577 --> 00:06:51,870
Yes.

76
00:06:58,293 --> 00:06:59,336
I see.

77
00:07:03,006 --> 00:07:04,424
I'm happy for you.

78
00:07:06,259 --> 00:07:09,346
You chose the same path as everybody.

79
00:07:11,056 --> 00:07:12,682
What about you, Nakamura?

80
00:07:25,654 --> 00:07:26,738
Okay, then.

81
00:07:27,238 --> 00:07:28,823
Good luck.

82
00:07:34,663 --> 00:07:35,955
Wait!

83
00:07:40,585 --> 00:07:41,753
Sawa,

84
00:07:42,253 --> 00:07:43,630
I...

85
00:07:44,130 --> 00:07:46,633
I don't have anything to do with you, but,

86
00:07:47,967 --> 00:07:49,010
still...

87
00:07:53,848 --> 00:07:55,141
it makes me sad.

88
00:07:56,393 --> 00:07:58,103
Watching you,

89
00:07:59,312 --> 00:08:00,563
it makes me sad,

90
00:08:01,272 --> 00:08:02,273
and it's painful.

91
00:08:03,817 --> 00:08:05,276
It's not sympathy or anything.

92
00:08:06,069 --> 00:08:07,070
It's because...

93
00:08:08,154 --> 00:08:10,365
it's as if I'm watching my past self.

94
00:08:12,742 --> 00:08:13,868
Sawa...

95
00:08:20,166 --> 00:08:23,336
There's a path for you
to live on with Kasuga.

96
00:08:24,879 --> 00:08:25,922
Because...

97
00:08:26,548 --> 00:08:27,924
the two of you are...

98
00:08:28,508 --> 00:08:29,925
probably...

99
00:08:29,926 --> 00:08:31,094
more than anyone else...

100
00:08:33,596 --> 00:08:34,764
If...

101
00:08:39,352 --> 00:08:41,938
If the two of you can live together...

102
00:08:45,150 --> 00:08:46,192
That'd be...

103
00:08:46,735 --> 00:08:47,736
the best for...

104
00:08:57,912 --> 00:08:59,080
The best for...

105
00:09:18,892 --> 00:09:19,976
Kasuga?

106
00:09:41,331 --> 00:09:42,624
Nakamura...

107
00:09:44,959 --> 00:09:47,212
I can't hold on to anything.

108
00:09:49,089 --> 00:09:50,465
No matter how much I try.

109
00:09:52,217 --> 00:09:54,302
Even when I can practically feel it.

110
00:09:56,262 --> 00:09:58,223
The moment I think I'm there,

111
00:09:59,099 --> 00:10:00,517
the journey begins again.

112
00:10:03,770 --> 00:10:04,813
So...

113
00:10:07,941 --> 00:10:10,401
That's why it still makes me happy...

114
00:10:13,613 --> 00:10:16,240
to see that you haven't left this world.

115
00:10:55,572 --> 00:10:56,573
Kasuga!

116
00:11:25,435 --> 00:11:26,436
What the...

117
00:12:30,667 --> 00:12:32,168
Kasuga...

118
00:12:34,337 --> 00:12:38,007
Don't you ever come again, boring human.

119
00:12:47,475 --> 00:12:48,643
Thank you.

120
00:12:54,065 --> 00:12:55,483
Thank you.

121
00:13:38,192 --> 00:13:40,987
THE CASE OF THE SERIAL KILLER GHOST

122
00:14:16,439 --> 00:14:18,565
A FEW YEARS LATER

123
00:14:18,566 --> 00:14:22,611
KASUGA

124
00:14:22,612 --> 00:14:24,154
Here you go.

125
00:14:24,155 --> 00:14:25,447
Thank you.

126
00:14:25,448 --> 00:14:26,574
Thank you, come again.

127
00:14:27,450 --> 00:14:29,743
Say, Kasuga,

128
00:14:29,744 --> 00:14:31,662
let's remember to smile, all right?

129
00:14:32,288 --> 00:14:34,248
Right! Sorry, sir.

130
00:14:39,670 --> 00:14:41,047
Welcome!

131
00:14:51,641 --> 00:14:52,725
Let's eat.

132
00:15:13,079 --> 00:15:15,956
It's so hot! I'm gonna melt!

133
00:15:17,458 --> 00:15:19,668
Hot, hot, hot!

134
00:15:21,629 --> 00:15:22,712
Here you go.

135
00:15:22,713 --> 00:15:23,881
Thanks.

136
00:15:31,472 --> 00:15:34,307
Ugh. Expired leftovers
from your job again?

137
00:15:34,308 --> 00:15:37,394
Come on, that can't be good for you.

138
00:15:37,395 --> 00:15:38,479
I know.

139
00:15:40,523 --> 00:15:41,732
Oh...

140
00:15:43,651 --> 00:15:45,194
What's this notebook for?

141
00:15:45,862 --> 00:15:46,988
That?

142
00:15:47,989 --> 00:15:50,365
I haven't written anything in it yet.

143
00:15:50,366 --> 00:15:51,951
Okay...

144
00:15:52,952 --> 00:15:54,370
And, what's the plan for it?

145
00:15:54,954 --> 00:15:56,246
I don't know.

146
00:15:56,247 --> 00:15:57,956
Okay.

147
00:15:57,957 --> 00:16:01,252
You should just start writing, you know.
Whatever comes to mind.

148
00:16:01,836 --> 00:16:04,880
I don't have your talent, Tokiwa.

149
00:16:04,881 --> 00:16:06,048
Me?

150
00:16:06,549 --> 00:16:08,008
I don't have any talent.

151
00:16:08,009 --> 00:16:11,429
No, I think your
new piece was really good.

152
00:16:11,804 --> 00:16:13,139
I hope you get that award.

153
00:16:16,601 --> 00:16:17,893
I'll poke your eyes out!

154
00:16:17,894 --> 00:16:19,936
Hey!

155
00:16:19,937 --> 00:16:22,439
What was that weak wail?

156
00:16:22,440 --> 00:16:23,732
That's not safe, you know.

157
00:16:23,733 --> 00:16:24,983
Baba's overhead chop!

158
00:16:24,984 --> 00:16:26,444
Wow, that's old school!

159
00:16:27,153 --> 00:16:28,653
Boom.

160
00:16:28,654 --> 00:16:30,114
Cut it out already.

161
00:16:34,493 --> 00:16:39,207
♪ Up and down, left and right
Make a circle and... ♪

162
00:16:43,085 --> 00:16:44,212
Hey.

163
00:16:44,879 --> 00:16:46,464
Can I stay the night?

164
00:16:48,216 --> 00:16:49,217
Sure.

165
00:16:54,931 --> 00:16:56,598
Hey, Kasuga?

166
00:16:56,599 --> 00:16:57,642
Yeah?

167
00:16:58,184 --> 00:16:59,185
What is it?

168
00:17:05,191 --> 00:17:06,317
Nothing.

169
00:17:08,110 --> 00:17:09,445
Nevermind.

170
00:17:10,988 --> 00:17:11,989
Okay.

171
00:17:18,496 --> 00:17:19,872
Hold me.

172
00:17:23,542 --> 00:17:24,543
Sure.

173
00:17:30,007 --> 00:17:31,342
Kasuga.

174
00:17:32,176 --> 00:17:33,219
Yeah?

175
00:17:35,721 --> 00:17:37,056
You know how I told you

176
00:17:37,974 --> 00:17:41,643
I wanted to see the town you were born in?

177
00:17:41,644 --> 00:17:43,062
Do you remember that?

178
00:17:44,689 --> 00:17:45,773
Yeah.

179
00:17:49,902 --> 00:17:51,070
Take me.

180
00:17:51,571 --> 00:17:52,613
Tomorrow.

181
00:17:56,033 --> 00:17:57,994
There's nothing there to see.

182
00:18:03,916 --> 00:18:06,294
You say that because you know the town.

183
00:18:08,588 --> 00:18:10,756
I don't know a thing about the place.

184
00:18:13,301 --> 00:18:14,885
You mentioned, some time,

185
00:18:17,179 --> 00:18:19,599
that the town was surrounded by mountains,

186
00:18:20,558 --> 00:18:23,686
so you always wanted to go
beyond those mountains.

187
00:18:25,646 --> 00:18:26,647
But...

188
00:18:29,525 --> 00:18:31,110
to me...

189
00:18:32,862 --> 00:18:35,406
your hometown is the other side.

190
00:19:42,098 --> 00:19:44,100
USED BOOKS AND GALLERY
NEKOMACHI-DO

191
00:20:31,731 --> 00:20:32,857
How was it?

192
00:20:35,901 --> 00:20:39,196
Did it look different to you,
seeing it now?

193
00:20:40,573 --> 00:20:41,657
I'm not sure...

194
00:20:43,534 --> 00:20:44,994
It looks the same,

195
00:20:46,328 --> 00:20:47,663
but, it also feels different.

196
00:20:50,541 --> 00:20:52,126
Think you can write something?

197
00:20:52,752 --> 00:20:53,753
What?

198
00:20:55,963 --> 00:20:57,798
I think it must be here.

199
00:20:58,883 --> 00:21:00,926
The thing only you can write.

200
00:21:05,723 --> 00:21:07,767
The people born in this town,

201
00:21:09,226 --> 00:21:10,895
live their lives in this town,

202
00:21:12,104 --> 00:21:13,856
and then die in this town.

203
00:21:16,484 --> 00:21:17,818
But, I...

204
00:21:20,237 --> 00:21:22,364
I couldn't live on in this town.

205
00:21:25,367 --> 00:21:28,579
I couldn't find a life
for Nakamura or Saeki, either.

206
00:21:30,206 --> 00:21:31,624
I couldn't save anyone.

207
00:21:33,292 --> 00:21:35,252
I couldn't live a proper life,

208
00:21:36,629 --> 00:21:39,089
nor could I become a true pervert, either.

209
00:21:40,257 --> 00:21:42,218
- I just kept running--
- Shut up.

210
00:21:42,843 --> 00:21:43,969
Shit bug.

211
00:21:44,637 --> 00:21:45,846
Shut up and write.

212
00:21:57,316 --> 00:21:59,652
Write about that shitty life.

213
00:22:01,028 --> 00:22:03,447
Live that shitty life.

214
00:22:04,782 --> 00:22:08,911
Live out that shitty life
for many years to come.

215
00:22:10,871 --> 00:22:13,665
What's that face for?

216
00:22:13,666 --> 00:22:16,919
You don't need to think it's fun.

217
00:22:17,503 --> 00:22:20,589
Because it'll be fun for me.

218
00:22:44,864 --> 00:22:46,949
Well, how about this?

219
00:22:47,616 --> 00:22:51,244
A dead boy
is reincarnated as a girl, and...

220
00:23:23,527 --> 00:23:24,820
MIZUKOSHI DINER

221
00:23:43,088 --> 00:23:45,965
THE FLOWERS OF EVIL
BAUDELAIRE

222
00:23:45,966 --> 00:23:47,050
THE FLOWERS OF EVIL
THE END

223
00:23:47,051 --> 00:23:48,052
Translated by Yuka Kristi
